<br>
As many of you know, the Necromancers of Norrath have long felt that their profession has been cursed by the gods. Since the rediscovery of Kunark and the hidden powers and treasures therein they have steadily declined in power with respect to the more powerful foes faced in the rediscovered lands and beyond. Due to this they are a dying breed, unable to share in the glories of their comrades and guildmates.<br>
<br>
With this in mind, many of the most powerful Necromancers of Norrath have made the decision to petition the gods themselves to review their decisions and to bring back the dark glory of their profession.<br>
<br>
My request is a simple one. If you have a care for the plight of the Necromancers then read their petition <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://pub3.ezboard.com/fenlightenddarkmessageboardfrm4.showMessage?topicID=610.topic">Here</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--> and, if you find within yourself the will to do so, add you signature to the list.<br>
<br>
In the past this request has been met with acrimony. Please do not post replies to this thread as I rather it didn't become yet another reason to add to our moderators blood pressures. If you do not wish to read the petition or sign it then simply hit the 'back' button, flames and attacks have no place here.<br>
<br>
Malvan Klaive.<br>
Rogue of Freeport.<br>
Tarew Marr. <p>"The fool does not forgive, the wise man forgives and forgets, but the sage forgives without forgetting"
